    </p>
    
    <p>
    My background is in IT (information technology), but in the areas of C++
    systems programming as well as traditional system administration and
    systems management. After many years of doing that I wanted to move into
    something new, full-stack web development was the chosen
    <em>something new</em>.
    Note, coming to grips with full-stack web development has involved much
    time, learning and experimentation.
    </p>

    <p>
    The Platters application is my album collection converted into a
    database-backed web application with user login and commenting components.
    </p>

    <p>
    This application was developed, over an extended period, to put in practise
    self-taught web development knowledge gained from the following disparate
    sources:
      <ul>
        <li><p>Ruby on Rails Tutorial.</p></li>
        <li><p>Rails 4 in Action.</p></li>
        <li><p>A host of Codecademy courses.</p></li>
        <li><p>A host of Jumpstart lab courses.</p></li>
        <li><p>HTML5 books.</p></li>
        <li><p>Ruby books.</p></li>
        <li><p>JavaScript, CoffeeScript and jQuery books.</p></li>
      </ul>
    </p>

    <p>
    Also, developer-focused DevOps techniques and technologies were needed to
    deploy and host this application on a DigitalOcean droplet on the
    Internet.
    </p>

